            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <salute>G.</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>My son H. D. wishes much to continue at your works, where he has now had a months trial; I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be much obliged if you could send him the indenture for signature.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I beg to call your attention to one point.: my son has been for some time recently out of health &amp; his physician D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Andrew Clark of C. Sqe<ref target="#foot.f3"/> urges him strongly not to overexert at first &amp; he thinks that he will thus gradually gain strength.— My son is most desirous to enter your works; &amp; I am sure that he will never voluntarily be idle. Under these circumstances I trust that you will be so good as not to bind him to long hours of work.</p>
<p>Gentlemen | Your obliged &amp; obedi servt | C. D.<lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">May 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</p>
<p rend="left">Easton. &amp; Anderson | The Grove | Southwark | London</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
